node.text:
Hello! My name is Brandon Harrell (@iambrandon747) and I’m sharing content that I #MadeWithPhotoshop⁠
⁠
I began using Photoshop in 2017, mainly because I got tired of asking my friends to edit things for me all the time. From the moment I opened Photoshop, I knew I wanted to create images that can help people escape to places that you only see in your dreams. Even if it was only for a few seconds a day. For this image - I day dreamed about a magical waterfall in the clouds, that is home to a single swan. I love adding clouds, and a crescent moon to all my images. It brings me joy to know that the clouds and moon give people a sense of calmness, peace, and inspiration. Can’t wait to show you what else I #MadeWithPhotoshop⁠

node.text:
Peur Bleue - Inspired by Halley’s Comet by Billie Eilish

Hi everyone! It’s @camillehalluin again with more dreamy art I #MadeWithPhotoshop.⁠⁠

Dreams have always been a big part of my life alongside music. When I was a teenager, reality sometimes became too painful. So I would put on my headphones, play some tunes and escape into surreal worlds that I would create in my mind.⁠⁠

All of my artwork is inspired by music, and Photoshop has allowed me to bring my ideas to life. For this piece, I was inspired by Halley’s Comet by Billie Eilish, particularly the outro. It reminds me of the lullabies our parents would play us when we were kids. Keeping the dreams at bay, chasing the nightmares away. ⁠⁠

I have always found comfort in the night because dreams feel like the only place that I can really be myself. It’s where my imagination takes over and the magic happens; faceless characters, unrealistic proportions, surreal stories. ⁠⁠

So as I turn off my light, close my eyes and listen to Halley’s Comet, my bedroom starts changing, letting the darkness in. Then the next day, I head over to Photoshop and here it is!⁠⁠

Sweet dreams to you!

node.text:
Where Dreams Are Born - Inspired by King Wisp by Bent⁠
⁠
Hi everyone! I am @camillehalluin and I’m a French artist, based in Ireland. By day I’m a digital designer and by night, a surreal artist. Let’s dive into my dreams and see what I #MadeWithPhotoshop⁠
⁠
Today I would like to invite you to travel within your imagination. Close your eyes and picture where you would like to go. Then suddenly, the walls around you disappear, the music starts playing and the place is right behind you.⁠
⁠
Whenever I listen to music, images come to my mind and this is what I pictured listening to King Wisp by Bent.⁠
⁠
Whenever we read a book, watch a movie, listen to a song, we plant our dream seeds, patiently waiting for them to bloom. Then, when the night comes and you fall asleep, you start traveling to places you had never imagined you would go.⁠
⁠
I sometimes wish the worlds I dream of could come true. Thanks to Photoshop I am able to capture them and bring magic into our lives.⁠
⁠
So hop on board and dream with me!⁠
